HEADWORD: Humite
<hw>Hum"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named after Sir A.
<etsep>Hume</etsep>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a
transparent vitreous brown color, found in the ejected masses of
Vesuvius. It is a silicate of iron and magnesia, containing
fluorine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hummel</ent>⟦br⟧
